'''鹽鹼灘'''，又稱'''鹽沼'''，是沿海[[潮間帶|潮間帶]]和陸地間的一種[[生態系統|生態系統]]，[[海水|海水]]或[[鹹水|鹹水]]有規律地湧入流出地帶。這一地帶主要生長[[鹽土植物|鹽土植物]]。<ref name="adam">Adam, P (1990). Saltmarsh Ecology. Cambridge University Press. New York.</ref><ref name="woodroffe">Woodroffe, CD (2002). Coasts: form, process and evolution. Cambridge University Press. New York.</ref>這些植物是陸生植物且耐鹽鹼。在水域[[食物鏈|食物鏈]]及海陸營養交換中鹽鹼灘扮演著重要的地位，此外次地帶也為一些陸地生物的生存提供了支持。同時它起著[[海岸保護|海岸保護]]的作用。<ref name="woodroffe"/>

鹽鹼灘常出現在[[溫帶|溫帶]]和[[極地|極地]]的海岸線上，<ref name="allen">Allen, JRL, Pye, K (1992). Saltmarshes: morphodynamics, conservation, and engineering significance. Cambridge University Press. Cambridge, UK.</ref>有穩固、形成和淹沒三種狀態。通常鹽鹼灘有河流帶來的沉積物形成的砂基或泥基，<ref name="chapman">Chapman, V. J. (1974). Salt marshes and salt deserts of the world. Phyllis Claire Chapman, Germany.</ref>且處於[[障壁島|障壁島]]、路堤、河口等有遮蔽之處。[[熱帶|熱帶]]和[[亞熱帶|亞熱帶]]因有[[紅樹林|紅樹林]]而不易形成鹽鹼灘，因為後者的生態是以[[草本植物|草本植物]]為主導的。<ref name="adam">Adam, P (1990). Saltmarsh Ecology. Cambridge University Press. New York.</ref>

大多數鹽鹼灘的地勢和海拔都很低，因為地帶空曠，所以常有大量人口聚集。<ref name="bromberg">Bromberg-Gedan, K., Silliman, B. R., and Bertness, M. D. (2009). Centuries of human driven change in salt marsh ecosystems, ''Annual Review of Marine Science'', 1: 117-141.</ref>根據實際地貌的差異，鹽鹼灘又可分為[[三角洲|三角洲]]、開闊海岸、海灣和[[溺灣|溺灣]]等等。歐洲等河流眾多之處常見有三角洲鹽鹼灘。<ref name="woodroffe">Woodroffe, CD (2002). Coasts: form, process and evolution. Cambridge University Press. New York.</ref><ref name="te ara">Te Ara - The Encyclopedia of New Zealand (2005-2010). [http://www.teara.govt.nz/en/estuaries/3 Plants of the Estuary] {{Wayback|url=http://www.teara.govt.nz/en/estuaries/3 |date=20121105073653 }}. Retrieved 15 March 2010</ref>

==成因==

潮灘隨著沉積物不斷堆積而升高，漸漸可以生長植物，<ref name="pethick">Pethick, J. (1984). An introduction to coastal geomorphology. Edward Arnold, London.</ref>隨著[[先鋒種|先鋒種]][[繁殖體|繁殖體]]的到達，此地生態開始改善。河流帶來懸浮泥沙，<ref name="chapman"/>[[藍綠藻|藍綠藻]]可以固著沉積物，<ref name="ginsburg">Ginsburg, R. N., and Lowenstam, H. A. (1958). The influence of marine bottom communities on the [[Deposition_(geology)|depositional]] environment of sediments. ''The Journal of Geology'', 66: (3), 310-318.</ref>加上新生的植物，<ref name="bird">Bird, E. (2008). Coastal geomorphology: an introduction. John Wiley & Sons Ltd, West Sussex, England.</ref>更使得堤岸愈來愈穩固。<ref name="aspden">Aspden, R. J., Vardy, S. and Paterson, D. M. (2004). Salt marsh microbial ecology: microbes, benthic mats and sediment movement. In Fagherazzi, S., Marani, M. and Blum, L. K. (Eds), ''The Ecogeomorphology of Tidal Marshes'' (pp. 115-136). American Geophysical Union, Washington, DC.</ref>

==潮汐與植被帶==
[[File:Bride-Brook-Salt-Marsh-s.jpg|thumb]][[大西洋|大西洋]]沿岸的鹽鹼灘]]
沿海鹽鹼地與普通土地最大的區別在於其每日都有[[潮汐|潮汐]]沖刷，造成該地持續積水。<ref name="adam"/>這對鹽鹼地的營養積累有著重要積極影響。<ref name="bromberg"/>除去這些[[低沼澤|低沼澤]]外，[[高沼澤|高沼澤]]因為地勢較高可以減少潮汐沖刷的影響，因而鹽度較低。<ref name="adam"/>實際上鹽鹼灘的鹽度依據氣候時間的不同也會發生變化，例如下雨可以減少鹽度而蒸發則使其增加。<ref name="adam"/>因此根據生理適應能力的不同，該地帶會形成不同的小環境。一般來說地勢較低處的植被耐鹽鹼度較高，也可以承受水的浸泡。<ref name="bertness">Bertness, MD, Ewanchuk, PJ, Silliman, BR (2002). Anthropogenic modification of New England salt marsh landscapes. ''Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences'' '''99(3):''' 1395-1398.</ref><ref name="rand">Rand, TA (2000). Seed Dispersal, Habitat Suitability and the Distribution of Halophytes across a Salt Marsh Tidal Gradient. ''Journal of Ecology'' '''88(4):''' 608-621.</ref>
